t4221.text: Juventus midfielder had two goals disallowed for offside but the first one would have counted as a goal if VAR existed. Salvatore Schillaci was offside but he was not.

t4222.text: Marco Osio was my pick for MOTM. Scored the decisive second goal and he was influential throughout the game. His passing was a joy to watch. Daniele Zoratto had a fine game in the regista role and Alberto Di Chiara had a great game at LWB.

t4223.text: It was hard to say if anyone had a sub-par game for Parma. Marco Ballotta made a few routine saves but he nearly botched a clearance and fortunately had some assistance from Luigi Apolloni.

t4224.text: Parma played some exciting football under Nevio Scala. They played in a 1-4-3-2 formation, they played at a high tempo, and their ball use was very tidy too.

t4225.text: The Ducali dominated the game and the Bianconeri only started to show some fight in the second half. Peruzzi was incredible and Juve probably would have lost at least 6-0 if he was out of form.

t4226.text: Around the 75th minute of the game, it says on the screen that Parma had eight shots on target to Juve's seven but it doesn't reflect on the quality of Parma's chances and play as well as Angelo Peruzzi's saves.
